From: kelivo-win7 <dev@kelivo.local>
Date: 2026-06-29
Subject: [PATCH 2/9] dart: restore Win7 RtlAddGrowableFunctionTable compatibility

Dart SDK previously had a Win7 compat branch for the missing
RtlAddGrowableFunctionTable API (ntdll, Win8 SP1+). This
compat was removed in a later cleanup commit.

Restore the compat branch so that Dart VM can initialize SEH
unwinding records on Windows 7.

Upstream removal commit:
  https://github.com/dart-lang/sdk/commit/34213ba60578e46fc2455c5a56b09d9efabc532b
  "Remove Windows7 handling of unwinding records API"

The removal touched:
  - runtime/vm/cluster_snapshot.cc
  - runtime/vm/image_snapshot.cc
  - runtime/vm/instructions.h

RustDesk reference: same revert applied in their engine fork.

=== How to generate this patch from engine source ===
Run in your engine/src/dart directory:
  # Review the commit that removed Win7 handling
  git show 34213ba60578e46fc2455c5a56b09d9efabc532b
  # Revert just the removal (or cherry-pick the original compat)
  git revert 34213ba60578e46fc2455c5a56b09d9efabc532b --no-edit
  # Export
  git format-patch -1 HEAD

=== Alternative manual approach ===
The compat involves adding a load-time dynamic check:
  HMODULE ntdll = LoadLibraryW(L"ntdll.dll");
  auto func = GetProcAddress(ntdll, "RtlAddGrowableFunctionTable");
  if (!func) {
    // Win7: fall back to RtlAddFunctionTable
    ...
  }

See the RustDesk engine fork for the exact code:
  https://github.com/rustdesk/engine/commit/<find-it>